This paper focuses on privacy analysis of business process models, which involves analyzing the flow of information within a system. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses privacy concerns and the need for privacy-enhanced models, which could fall under the category of cyber security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper describes the implementation of Pleak, which involves programming language concepts and techniques (cs.PL).
